[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In the old days, when I was building out my home lab, I used to gravitate towards old used enterprise gear because it came with something called IPMI built right into the motherboard. That gave me a keyboard, mouse and video access to the remote machine no matter where I was over the network. However, these days you can do that exact same thing with something like this.'

[00:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is the GLINet Comet. This is the PoE version I have right here. So essentially, you can power this little box using just nothing but this ethernet port right here'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from your PoE switch. And then you connect up the HDMI input and the USB input directly into the back of your computer, and you can control the thing as if you were sat physically at the console of the machine.'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, the cool bit for me at least is that this thing can run TailScale. So guess what? We\'re gonna plug this in, see how it works, and try and get TailScale set up on this bad boy in today\'s video.'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, I\'m not expecting setup to be terribly difficult today. The box comes with everything that you need to get started, which includes an Ethernet cable, an HDMI cable, and I\'m actually happy to report,'

[01:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compared to some of the other options on the market, like the Jet KVM, that this uses full-size HDMI. It just takes the edge off the Jet KVM for me, is that you have to use that sort of mini, or is it micro HDMI.'

[01:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Anyway, and then this also comes with two USB-C cables, because even though this device is officially POE rated, it\'s also got a little 5-volt, 2-amp USB-C plug on the side as well,'

[01:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in case you can\'t give it POE power. So the ports on this thing are really straightforward. There\'s a USB 2.0 port, so if you want to mount any kind of storage. An HDMI in-port, although there\'s no pass-through,'

[01:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which their more expensive Kickstarter-backed Comet Pro, which I\'ll put on the screen right now, That has 4K HDMI pass-through, so you could literally put this between the computer and a real physical monitor. So, I don\'t know, a parent\'s house or something like that might be really useful for that use case.'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You\'ve got a USB-C port here for the HID device, the HID device, and then, of course, the Ethernet port for PoE in. And then on the side, it\'s just a 5-volt, 2-amp USB-C plug.'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
