AUDIO: 'through the Comet. Actually, that\'s pretty interesting. Rather than running an Apple TV or something like that as an exit node, I can now route all of the traffic from my client devices out through the Comet in the network'

[07:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that the comet sat in, could be pretty useful. Would be handy though, if we could have comet be backed by a proper TLS certificate, wouldn\'t it? So I wonder, can I drop into the terminal of the comet and do tail scale serve dash dash BG,'

[07:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'well I guess 443? I don\'t think that\'s gonna work actually \'cause if I do grep 443, the error message tells me it might have worked.'

[07:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I guess we\'ll find out in a minute. Yeah, plain HTTP request was sent. Let me go back to the toolbox and then access the terminal again. Now that failed because actually if I thought about it,'

[08:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the comment\'s running on a self-signed certificate. So what we actually need to do is effectively do this, but just modify the command ever so slightly to be on the correct port.'

[08:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So let\'s do this and then modify this to be 443 And then do dash dash BG as well, because I want it in the background. And now I\'m hopeful that this will work. So there we go.'

[08:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'All right, so it\'s just a couple of little tweaks. So because Comet is running a self-signed TLS certificate and the chain of trust doesn\'t end anywhere, like the CA that is generated as part of the self-signed certificate chain, there is no trusted CA'

[08:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as part of the TLS validation chain. We have to put that insecure option in there, but essentially you can now access your KVM, your GLINet Comet KVM with a full TLS certificate'

[08:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just by running this one simple command. Maybe that should be the title in the thumbnail. You won\'t believe this one simple trick. I will not do clickbait on this channel.'

[09:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s just, I just won\'t, I won\'t do it. That\'s my contract to you as the viewer. this is the command that you want here. So you drop to the terminal, which is found under toolbox and then terminal and access.'

[09:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And then you type this command in here, tail scale serve dash dash BG to put it in the background. And then HTTPS insecure localhost port 443. And that\'s it.'

[09:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You can now access your KVM with a proper TLS certificate. So I think that\'s a really quick overview. I mean, I should also point out that GLINet have their own proprietary cloud service, which I don\'t know, I\'m just gonna use Tailscale'

[09:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
